Sentencas: The overpotential at low currents is investigated with several 100 cm(2) class commercial solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Effect of water on the anodic overpotential at low currents in a solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The water content, H-2 and O-2 partial pressures, and reactant flow rates are experimental parameters.
Titulo: Effect of water on the anodic overpotential at low currents in a solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: In the current- voltage curves, there is very steep voltage drop and a large overpotential in the low current regions for the dry H-2 gas.
Titulo: Effect of water on the anodic overpotential at low currents in a solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: On the other hand, the 3% H2O contained H-2 gas results in a significantly reduced overpotential in the same low current region.
Titulo: Effect of water on the anodic overpotential at low currents in a solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Theoretically and experimentally the charge transfer resistance is obtained at the anode, which indicates that the anode kinetics is not the reason for the large overpotential at low currents.
Titulo: Effect of water on the anodic overpotential at low currents in a solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Changes in H-2 and O-2 partial pressures do not have any significant effects on the current-voltage curves.
Titulo: Effect of water on the anodic overpotential at low currents in a solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: We conclude that the overpotential at low currents is attributed to the mass transfer resistance of water species.
Titulo: Effect of water on the anodic overpotential at low currents in a solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Theoretical calculation of anodic overpotential also supports the experimental results.
Titulo: Effect of water on the anodic overpotential at low currents in a solid oxide fuel cell
